China Construction, Gome, Posco, Solargiga: Asia Ex-Japan Equity Preview

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-03-28T23:56:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/china-construction-gome-posco-solargiga-asia-ex-japan-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Asian trading, excluding  Japan .
Stock symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close, unless noted otherwise.  China Construction Bank Corp. (939)  (939 HK): The world’s second-
largest lender by market value may have 700 billion yuan ($107
billion) to 750 billion yuan of new loans this year, Vice
President Chen Zuofu said at a briefing in Beijing. The lender
had no refinancing plans for this year, President Zhang Jianguo
said at the briefing. The shares declined 2.3 percent to
HK$7.15.  ECS ICT Bhd. (ECS)  : The Malaysian distributor of
computer-related products said it has been awarded distribution
rights for Apple Inc.’s iPad in the Southeast Asian nation. ECS
was unchanged at 1.54 ringgit.  Gome Electrical Appliances Holdings Ltd. (493)  (493 HK): China’s
second-biggest electronics retailer said profit rose 39 percent
to 1.96 billion yuan last year as consumer demand for home
appliances climbed. That compares with the 1.97 billion yuan
average of eight analysts’ estimates compiled by Bloomberg.
Sales rose 19 percent to 50.9 billion yuan. Gome fell 1.6
percent to HK$2.54.  Green Energy Technology Inc. (3519)  (3519 TT): The company’s board
approved plans for the early repurchase of all outstanding first
unsecured convertible bonds at a price of NT$100,000 ($3,391),
the company said in an e-mailed statement. The shares climbed
5.7 percent to NT$139.5.  Jaya Tiasa Holdings Bhd. (JT)  : The Malaysian timber
producer and oil palm planter said net income in the third
quarter ended Jan. 31 almost tripled from a year earlier to 39.9
million ringgit ($13 million) on higher selling prices. Jaya
gained 6.2 percent to 6.16 ringgit.  Posco (005490 KS): The world’s third-biggest steelmaker by
output boosted its heavy-plate capacity by 40 percent,
overtaking Japan’s JFE Holdings Inc. as the biggest producer of
the sheets used mostly to build ships. The completion of a 2
million metric ton plant lifted total capacity for the plates to
7 million tons a year, the Pohang, South Korea-based company
said in a statement.  Posco (005490)  rallied 2.8 percent to 516,000 won.  Solargiga Energy Holdings Ltd. (757)  (757 HK): The Chinese solar
ingot and wafer maker reported full-year net income of 214
million yuan in 2010, compared with a loss of 98 million yuan a
year earlier, according to a filing to the Hong Kong stock
exchange. Solargiga climbed 1.1 percent to HK$1.84.  To contact the reporter on this story:
